Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the
@rigatoni pasta{180%g}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%mins}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and
equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Once browned, stir in the garlic and @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if
you'd prefer things milder). Cook for ~{1%min} more.

While the chicken cooks, add the rigatoni to your pan of boiling water.
Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the #pan{}. Drizzle with
@oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Stir the @finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%g},
@water for the sauce{100%ml} and @sugar{1%tsp} for the sauce into the pan with
the chicken.

Bring to the boil, stir and lower the heat so the sauce simmers gently.

Cook until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce has thickened,
~{10-12%mins}. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @baby spinach{40%g} a handful at a
time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Add half of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and the @butter{20%g}
and mix vigorously until the both have melted.

When your pasta is ready, share between your #serving bowls{}.

Top by sprinkling over the remaining hard Italian style cheese.

Enjoy!